This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a novel approach for detecting out-of-distribution examples using a deep neural network architecture. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the state-of-the-art method for novelty detection in image datasets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the use of density models, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Furthermore, the paper involves the use of residual networks, which is a popular topic in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method in terms of true positive rate and true negative rate, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
